name: Warung Belayag "Primadewi Veteran"
address: Jl. Veteran, Padang Kerta, Kec. Karangasem, Kabupaten Karangasem, Bali 80811, Indonesia
review 1: This is a must-place-to-visit on my way to Karangasem. Open at 07.00 to 16.30 wita. They provide the best "blayag" I've ever tasted. Blayag is made of rice, wrapped in a coconut leaf, and steamed. The texture is tender and savory. Try the "belimbing wuluh" leaf that was cooked with spices. They also provide 'tok tok chicken' and 'nasi campur'.

name: Taman Jagath Karana
address: HH5R+9C3, Jl. Veteran, Padang Kerta, Kec. Karangasem, Kabupaten Karangasem, Bali 80811, Indonesia
review 1:
An beautiful park located in Karangasem Regency. Equipped with the iconic Panca Dewata statues, this place provides free wifi facilities for all visitors, a children's playground, and is great for a free stroll. The majestic view of Mount Agung can also be seen from here. This park is also suitable for sports.
Its location is very strategic as it is located on Jalur 11 Karangasem, in the middle of Karangasem Regency. Around Jalur 11, there are many people selling snacks and light meals, so you will never go hungry when you visit here.
I highly recommend this place to be visited because it is free and has great facilities.
review 2: Very good playground for families especially for children in Karangasem district, easy to access, there is a playground for children, there is a skate park, jogging track, close to the football stadium, but there are facilities that are not well maintained, some benches are broken, hopefully could be improve in the future
review 3: Good for kids play and there's sitting arrangements bring your food and enjoy even charge point there bring charger and use it it's under circle table
review 4: This place nice for plying with children and also hv many small restaurant
review 5: Good place for relax and children playground also free wifi..need more care abt the rabish

name: MAB
address: Jl Veteran Jalur 11, Padang Kerta, Karangasem, Karangasem Regency, Bali 80811, Indonesia
review 1: Pondok Mina Abianbase is a great place to eat for family time.  The place is quite spacious, comfortable and clean. There is a fish pond that can entertain childrens so they don't get bored.  I have come here many times with my parents and family.  Here offers a variety of processed carp menus such as fried carp balado packages, sweet and sour carp packages, fried carp packages, MKD carp packages and others, the prices offered are also affordable.  The taste of the carp seasoning remains consistent and nothing has changed, it tastes good and satisfies customers.  The downside is that the service is a bit slow. Beside eat there, we can also take away.

review 2: Wonderful local food, brilliant prices and a beautiful setting looking over the rice fields! We highly recommend if you‚Äôre in the area!
review 3:
We enjoyed our dinner at this local restaurant. The food was delicious and the prices much better than at the restaurants around Tirta Gangga.
We are glad that we found this restaurant where we had the chance to taste real local cuisine at decent prices.
